Project Structure
SCL_Project/
│
├─ scl_scanner.py       # Main file that runs the scanner
├─ tokens.py            # Person 1: token definitions and classification
├─ scanner.py           # Person 2: scanner logic
├─ output.py            # Person 3: printing and JSON output
└─ hello_world.scl      # Sample SCL input file

Group Roles & Responsibilities 

Person 1 — Token Definitions (tokens.py)

Define all keywords, operators, and special characters.

Write a function get_token_type(word) that returns the type of each word.

Example token types: keyword, operator, special_char, number, identifier.



Person 2 — Scanner Logic (scanner.py)

Read the SCL source file from command line input.

Use get_token_type to classify each word as a token.

Return a list of tokens for further processing.




Person 3 — Output & Report (output.py)

Print the list of tokens to the console.

Save the tokens as a JSON file.

Document the grammar of the SCL subset in BNF/EBNF.

Create a sample report with screenshots and example input/output.
